President Barack Obama has proclaimed November 2015 as National Native American Heritage Month. In his proclamation, he recognizes the contributions made by Native Americans to the country and acknowledges the injustices they have faced in the past. The President highlights his efforts to strengthen the government-to-government relationship with tribal nations and improve the lives of Native youth. He also mentions initiatives to address vital gaps in resources for Indian Country and protect communities from the threat of climate change. President Obama calls upon all Americans to commemorate the month with appropriate programs and activities and to celebrate November 27, 2015, as Native American Heritage Day.